            "note": "CREMA processes raw data of a set of samples (FASTQ) from chromatin accessibility (ATAC/DNase-seq) or enhancer mark (ChIP-seq) data.  Results include all identified CREs and, for each regulatory motif, inferred activities across the input samples, predicted genome-wide targets, CRE to gene associations, enriched pathways and functional classes of genes, and direct interactions between regulators. All results are presented within interactive and easily navigable HTML pages. Full results are also available for download.",
